# Homelab App Backup Procedure
## Immich & Paperless-NGX → TrueNAS → pCloud

---

## 1. Purpose

This document describes how to implement **application-level backups for Immich and Paperless-NGX** and upload them to **pCloud** while ensuring that:

- Backups **do not reside permanently on the Debian Docker VM**
- Backups are stored **first on TrueNAS**
- **rclone on the Debian VM** uploads the backups to pCloud
- Backup data remains **separated from VM-level backups**

This provides an additional safety layer beyond Proxmox Backup Server (PBS).

---

## 2. Architecture Overview

The backup pipeline follows this flow:

```
Applications (Immich / Paperless)
        │
        ▼
Export scripts (Debian Docker VM)
        │
        ▼
Debian VM (NFS mount)
/mnt/truenas-app-backups
        │
        ▼
TrueNAS dataset
/mnt/tank/backups/app-exports
        │
        ▼
rclone upload
        │
        ▼
pCloud off-site storage
```

**Important design principle:**

- **Debian VM acts only as a transport node**
- **TrueNAS is the storage authority**

