## 16. Log Rotation

Without log rotation, backup logs will grow indefinitely. Create a logrotate configuration covering all four log files:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/logrotate.d/homelab-backups
```

Configuration:

```
/var/log/pcloud-export-backup.log
/var/log/pcloud-integrity-check.log
/var/log/paperless-backup.log
/var/log/immich-backup.log
{
    weekly
    rotate 12
    compress
    missingok
    notifempty
    dateext
    create 0644 root root
}
```

| Option | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `weekly` | rotate once per week |
| `rotate 12` | keep 12 weeks of logs |
| `compress` | gzip older log files |
| `missingok` | no error if log file is absent |
| `notifempty` | skip rotation if log is empty |
| `dateext` | append date to rotated filename |
| `create 0644 root root` | recreates log file after rotation with correct permissions |

Example rotated filenames:

```
pcloud-export-backup.log-2026-03-08.gz
pcloud-integrity-check.log-2026-03-08.gz
paperless-backup.log-2026-03-08.gz
immich-backup.log-2026-03-08.gz
```

