## 17. Enable ZFS Snapshot Protection

Snapshots protect backups from accidental deletion, ransomware, and script bugs.

In TrueNAS:

```
Data Protection → Periodic Snapshot Tasks → Add
```

Configuration:

```
Dataset:   tank/backups/app-exports
Schedule:  Every 6 hours
Lifetime:  30 days
```

At 4 snapshots per day over 30 days, this retains approximately **120 snapshots**. Snapshots use minimal storage due to ZFS copy-on-write — only blocks that have actually changed since the previous snapshot are stored.

**Manual snapshot access:**

```bash
ls /mnt/tank/backups/app-exports/.zfs/snapshot/
```

Each snapshot appears as a dated directory containing a full read-only view of the dataset at that point in time. Copy files directly from there to recover them without any restore tooling.

