## 18. Optional: Failure Alerting

Currently, failures are logged but produce no active notification. To add alerting, include a failure trap in each script after any existing `trap cleanup EXIT` line:

```bash
on_failure() {
    echo "ERROR: backup failed at $(date)" >&2
    # Uncomment and configure one of the following:
    # curl -d "backup failed" https://your-gotify-instance/message?token=TOKEN
    # curl -fsS -m 10 --retry 5 https://hc-ping.com/your-uuid/fail
}
trap on_failure ERR
```

Compatible notification options: Gotify, Healthchecks.io, ntfy, or a simple email via `mail`.

