## 19. Restore Procedures

### Restore Paperless

Download backup from pCloud:

```bash
rclone copy \
    pcloud:homelab-app-exports/paperless \
    /restore/paperless
```

Extract the most recent archive automatically:

```bash
mkdir -p /tmp/restore-paperless
LATEST=$(ls -t /restore/paperless/*.tar.gz 2>/dev/null | head -n1)
if [ -z "$LATEST" ]; then
    echo "ERROR: No Paperless backup archives found in /restore/paperless"
    exit 1
fi
tar -xzf "$LATEST" -C /tmp/restore-paperless
```

Or specify a date manually:

```bash
tar -xzf /restore/paperless/paperless-YYYY-MM-DD.tar.gz -C /tmp/restore-paperless
```

Run importer:

```bash
docker exec -it paperless-webserver-1 \
    python manage.py document_importer /tmp/restore-paperless
```

### Restore Immich

Download files from pCloud:

```bash
rclone copy \
    pcloud:homelab-app-exports/immich \
    /restore/immich
```

```bash
# 1. Stop application services only — keep the database container running.
#    docker compose down would stop immich_postgres, making docker exec fail.
docker compose stop immich-server immich-microservices

# 2. Wipe the current database and restore from dump.
docker exec -i immich_postgres dropdb -U postgres immich --if-exists
docker exec -i immich_postgres createdb -U postgres immich

# Automatically select the most recent database dump
LATEST_DB=$(ls -t /restore/immich/immich-db-dump-*.sql 2>/dev/null | head -n1)
if [ -z "$LATEST_DB" ]; then
    echo "ERROR: No Immich database dumps found in /restore/immich"
    exit 1
fi
echo "Restoring database from: $LATEST_DB"
docker exec -i immich_postgres psql -U postgres immich < "$LATEST_DB"

# 3. Restore library files
rsync -av /restore/immich/library/ /mnt/immich/library/

# 4. Restart all services
docker compose up -d
```

> **Important:** Do not run `docker compose down` before the database restore. If `immich_postgres` is stopped, `docker exec` will fail. Stop only the application services while leaving the database container running.

> **Version compatibility:** Restore into the same or newer version of Immich to avoid database schema incompatibilities.

