## 20. Emergency Restore Cheat Sheet

Use this section in a total disaster scenario where your Debian VM, TrueNAS dataset, or both have been wiped.

### Step 1 — Restore Infrastructure

Before running any restore commands, rebuild the foundation:

- **TrueNAS:** Re-create the `app-exports` dataset and NFS share as described in Sections 4 and 5.
- **Debian VM:** Re-mount the NFS share (Section 6) and verify `rclone` is installed and configured (Sections 7–8).

### Step 2 — Pull Everything Back from pCloud

```bash
# Ensure the mount directory exists after rebuilding the VM
mkdir -p /mnt/truenas-app-backups

# Pull all exports from pCloud back to TrueNAS
rclone copy pcloud:homelab-app-exports /mnt/truenas-app-backups -P
```

The `-P` flag shows live progress. This may take time depending on the size of your Immich library.

Verify the download completed before proceeding:

```bash
ls /mnt/truenas-app-backups
ls /mnt/truenas-app-backups/immich
ls /mnt/truenas-app-backups/paperless
```

Check that dataset sizes look reasonable:

```bash
du -sh /mnt/truenas-app-backups/*
```

A suspiciously small total (a few kilobytes) likely indicates an incomplete download or a mount failure. Do not proceed with a restore until the sizes match your expectations.

### Step 3 — Restore Paperless-NGX

```bash
# Verify the mount is available before restoring.
mountpoint -q /mnt/truenas-app-backups || {
    echo "ERROR: TrueNAS not mounted"
    exit 1
}

# 1. Extract the most recent backup automatically
mkdir -p /tmp/restore-paperless
LATEST=$(ls -t /mnt/truenas-app-backups/paperless/*.tar.gz 2>/dev/null | head -n1)
if [ -z "$LATEST" ]; then
    echo "ERROR: No Paperless backup archives found in /mnt/truenas-app-backups/paperless"
    exit 1
fi
echo "Restoring from: $LATEST"
tar -xzf "$LATEST" -C /tmp/restore-paperless

# 2. Run the importer
docker exec -it paperless-webserver-1 python manage.py document_importer /tmp/restore-paperless
```

To restore a specific date instead:

```bash
tar -xzf /mnt/truenas-app-backups/paperless/paperless-YYYY-MM-DD.tar.gz -C /tmp/restore-paperless
```

### Step 4 — Restore Immich

```bash
# 1. Stop application services — keep the database container running
docker compose stop immich-server immich-microservices

# 2. Wipe and restore the database
docker exec -i immich_postgres dropdb -U postgres immich --if-exists
docker exec -i immich_postgres createdb -U postgres immich

LATEST_DB=$(ls -t /mnt/truenas-app-backups/immich/immich-db-dump-*.sql 2>/dev/null | head -n1)
if [ -z "$LATEST_DB" ]; then
    echo "ERROR: No Immich database dumps found in /mnt/truenas-app-backups/immich"
    exit 1
fi
echo "Restoring database from: $LATEST_DB"
docker exec -i immich_postgres psql -U postgres immich < "$LATEST_DB"

# 3. Restore library files
rsync -av /mnt/truenas-app-backups/immich/library/ /mnt/immich/library/

# 4. Bring all services back up
docker compose up -d
```

> **Important:** The `dropdb` / `createdb` sequence ensures a clean restore. Always wipe and recreate before importing. Do not run `docker compose down` — this stops `immich_postgres` and makes `docker exec` fail.

